SIMPLE: c_q_d
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: C Q D
<hw>C Q D</hw>. <def>In radiotelegraphy, the letters signified by the
code call formerly used (cf. S O S) by ships in distress, formed by
combining the code call C Q (formerly used as a general call for all
stations) with D for distress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crab</ent>⟦br⟧
